edu.kit.cm.kitcampusguide.standardtypes
Class MapPosition

java.lang.Object
  edu.kit.cm.kitcampusguide.standardtypes.WorldPosition
      edu.kit.cm.kitcampusguide.standardtypes.MapPosition
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class MapPosition
extends WorldPosition

Represents a position on a Map. Extends WorldPosition. Stores a additionally to the longitude and latitude stored by WorldPosition. Positions representing the same longitude and latitude on the same map don't need to be the same object, rather, due to longitude and latitude being double, it's better to create a new MapPosition each time it is needed.

fred

calculateDistance

public static double calculateDistance(MapPosition pos1,
                                       MapPosition pos2)
Calculates the distance between to given MapPositions. If the positions are placed on different maps, Double.MAX_VALUE is returned. Otherwise the distance in meters as calculated in WorldPosition.calculateDistance(WorldPosition, WorldPosition) is returned.

Parameters:
pos1 - a MapPosition
pos2 - a MapPosition
Returns:
the distance between the two given points.
